# Kernel modules required for initramfs during secure boot provisioning
#
# Prefer kernel crypto API aliases (e.g. crypto-xts(aes)) over concrete
# module names. Aliases are resolved by libkmod via modules.alias and survive
# the upstream renames that happen across kernel releases — e.g.
# chacha-neon/chacha_generic in 6.12 vs the chacha consolidation in 6.18.
# Concrete names like aes-arm64 only need listing when no alias points at
# them; rpi-modcopy pulls in dependencies automatically.
#
# Lines starting with # are comments and are ignored.
# Empty lines are ignored.
#
# To override this list, copy it to /etc/rpi-sb-provisioner/kernel_modules.list

# Device mapper + userspace crypto socket (stable module names)
dm-crypt
algif_skcipher

# AES-XTS (default cipher). The alias resolves to xts + the best AES impl
# the kernel has — aes-arm64 on the Pi 5, aes_generic as fallback —
# without us needing to spell either out.
crypto-xts(aes)

# Adiantum (alternative cipher for devices without AES acceleration).
# Each alias pulls in its own dependencies: adiantum needs nhpoly1305 and
# a chacha variant, both of which have been renamed across kernel versions.
crypto-adiantum
crypto-nhpoly1305
crypto-xchacha12
